Serialized Form

  • Package projectone.demo.model

    • Class projectone.demo.model.Inventory

      class Inventory extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • id
          Long id
          Unique identifier for the Inventory item. It is marked with Id to indicate that this field is the primary key. It is automatically generated by the database.
        • lowThreshold
          Integer lowThreshold
          The low stock threshold. When inventory quantity falls below this value, it indicates that the item is running low. This field cannot be null.
        • name
          String name
          The name of the inventory item. This field cannot be null.
        • orderDate
          LocalDate orderDate
          The date on which the last order was made for this inventory item. This field helps in tracking when the item was last ordered. This field cannot be null.
        • quantity
          Integer quantity
          The quantity of the inventory item in stock. This field cannot be null.
        • type
          String type
          The type category of the inventory item. This field cannot be null.
        • unit
          String unit
          The unit of measurement for the inventory item quantity. This field cannot be null.

    • Class projectone.demo.model.Orders

      class Orders extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • order_id
          Long order_id
          Unique identifier for the order. This field serves as the primary key in the database table.
        • orderDatetime
          LocalDateTime orderDatetime
          The current status of the order (e.g., processing, completed, canceled). This field allows the system to track the progress and management of the order.
        • price
          BigDecimal price
          The total price of the order, stored as a BigDecimal to handle precise monetary calculations.
        • status
          String status
          The current status of the order (e.g., processing, completed, canceled). This field allows the system to track the progress and management of the order.
